value: Breeds in Africa south of the equatorial forest from Angola to Tangan- yika Territory and south to Damaraland and the Transvaal. Migrates across the forest to spend the non-breeding season in the grasslands of Nigeria, Cameroon, Belgian Congo and Uganda.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Intra-African migrant, mature woodland and wooded grassland: breeds Brachystegia Angola - S Tanzania south to NE Namibia, N Botswana, extreme NE South Africa; winters mainly SE Nigeria, Cameroon, S Chad east to Uganda; vagrant Gambia, E Sudan, S Somalia, C Cape Province.

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip
